-- Conergy Climbs After Agreeing With Creditors to Reduce Debt by Almost 60%
-- B y   T o d d   W h i t e   a n d   M i k e   G a v i n
-- 2010-12-20T10:33:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-20/conergy-climbs-after-agreeing-with-creditors-to-reduce-debt-by-almost-60-.html
Conergy AG  climbed as much as 27
percent in Frankfurt after the solar-module maker agreed with
creditors to reduce its debt by 188 million euros ($247
million).  Conergy shares surged as high as 62 euro cents and traded
at 60 cents, up 22 percent, as of 11:29 a.m. local time.  The company said in a statement released Dec. 17 that it
will reduce credit lines to 135 million euros from 323 million
euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
